text: hi everyone
Anthony Fantana here the Internet's

review this request has been hanging

maybe if you don't know this New York

that came out in 2010 some tracks off of
that got passed around the blogosphere a
lot very popular I even mentioned it on
my favorite EPS of 2010 lists so now
I've got 11 tracks in 33 minutes from
these guys and I could be wrong but I
think outside of the genre of children's
music this is probably the sunniest
album of 2011 there are a lot of things
that I could talk about with this LP in
terms of its style like how it tries to
go for an old-school pop sound with that
wall of sound technique and that high
gloss finish and lots of cute and
sentimental songs about friends enemies
and lovers there are a lot of very very
influenced melodies and chord
progressions all over this thing
tons of reverb pretty solid guitar tone
a little piano here and there maybe some
organ and this thing this plinky plinky
thing which is either a little baby
metal xylophone or a fisher-price piano
which is just mimicking whatever the
vocal melody is and hanging underneath
it chirping along for what I think is
every song and there are some modern
beats on here like on oh my god which
sounds like it could have been behind a
hip hop song and there are some
tried-and-true ones on here - like Most
Wanted which I could see backing up a
60s girl group and there's some standout
songwriting moments on the
thing to like go outside and oh my god
where the songs feel fleshed out
they just don't fade out after a verse

original it's memorable and it's catchy

band's songwriting sets them apart from

all just feels so familiar to me its

this LP might be the song you know what

hear nothing but but blue skies and
flower fields I know I've enjoyed sugary

my teeth are just falling out and it's
not really just the mood of this album
it's one thing piled on top of another
thing piled on top of another thing for
me the really cutesy instrumentation
adds to how fast this LP wears thin for
me and also Madeline fallens vocals
which are very light and fine to begin
with but how her voice is mixed and
produced on some of these tracks it's
like they're made to be light and fine
to the max it's like they're made to be
